com.edinarobotics.utils.gamepad

Class TwoAxisJoystick

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edinarobotics.utils.gamepad.Joystick
      • com.edinarobotics.utils.gamepad.TwoAxisJoystick
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FilteredTwoAxisJoystick

    public class TwoAxisJoystick
extends Joystick
    This class implements a simple interface for interacting with a 2-axis joystick. This interface was designed with the Logitech Attack 3 in mind. The buttons have been given names to avoid depending on their printed labels.

        getJoystickAxisState in class Joystick
        Returns:

      • getThrottle

        public double getThrottle()
        Returns the current value of the throttle axis of the joystick.
        A value of 0 indicates that the throttle lever is fully down. A value of 1 indicates that the throttle lever is fully up.
        Returns:
        The current value of the throttle axis of the joystick.
